modules.description: Provides functions to create a React Query client, wrap components with query context, and define a component that consumes the query client and context settings. Operates with React elements, query client instances, and configuration options. Used to set up a shared query client across React components with optional context propagation.

Creates a query client for managing asynchronous data fetching and caching. Accepts configuration options and returns a client instance tailored for React applications. Integrates with React components to enable real-time data updates and error handling.

Manages React Query integration by enabling client creation, context wrapping, and query-aware component definitions. Supports React elements, query clients, and configuration objects to centralize data fetching and caching. Allows components to access shared query instances and settings, enabling efficient data loading and state management. Example uses include fetching user data, caching API responses, and propagating query configurations across a component tree.
